/--
Lemma 3 school-cutoff fixed-point support.

The source equilibrium threshold in Equation (6) is a capacity cutoff for the
school's applicant mass.  This reusable support theorem isolates the
one-dimensional part: if applicant mass is continuous, strictly decreasing in
the school cutoff, tends to total potential mass at `-∞`, and tends to zero at
`+∞`, then there is a unique capacity-realizing cutoff; moreover the paper's
set `{z : applicantMass z ≤ capacity}` is exactly the upper threshold region.
-/
theorem paper_lemma3_school_cutoff_existsUnique_and_capacity_region_of_strictAnti_applicant_mass
    {applicantMass : ℝ → ℝ} {capacity totalApplicantMass : ℝ}
    (hcont : Continuous applicantMass)
    (hanti : StrictAnti applicantMass)
    (hatBot :
      Filter.Tendsto applicantMass Filter.atBot (nhds totalApplicantMass))
    (hatTop :
      Filter.Tendsto applicantMass Filter.atTop (nhds 0))
    (hcapacity : capacity ∈ Set.Ioo (0 : ℝ) totalApplicantMass) :
    ∃! admissionThreshold : ℝ,
      applicantMass admissionThreshold = capacity ∧
        ∀ z : ℝ,
          applicantMass z ≤ capacity ↔ admissionThreshold ≤ z :=
    existsUnique_eq_and_upper_region_of_continuous_strictAnti_tendsto_atBot_atTop
      hcont hanti hatBot hatTop hcapacity

/--
Proposition 2(i) school-threshold support for two schools.

Paper statement: each school's selection policy is an upper-threshold rule in
its own estimated skill.  This theorem packages the reusable capacity-cutoff
argument for two fixed applicant-mass functions.  The concrete strategic
fixed-point work is then to instantiate `applicantMass1` and `applicantMass2`
from the two-school applicant pools.
-/
theorem paper_proposition2_two_school_selection_thresholds_existUnique_and_capacity_regions_of_strictAnti_applicant_masses
    {applicantMass1 applicantMass2 : ℝ → ℝ}
    {capacity1 capacity2 totalApplicantMass1 totalApplicantMass2 : ℝ}
