/--
Proposition 5(ii), selected equation-(46) low/high threshold construction
from Gaussian upper-tail-mean source formulas.

This is the Gaussian source-facing version of
`paper_proposition5_low_and_high_cost_thresholds_of_selected_twoFull_merit_crossings_interval_of_ordered_merits`.
It proves the needed direct ordered-merit premises from concrete tail-mean
identifications plus scale/threshold comparisons, then constructs the paper's
ordered low/high full-sub cost thresholds.
