/--
Proposition 5(ii) / Theorem 3(ii) objective bridge with the two main source
case obligations discharged.

The both-groups condition-(13) branch is ruled out by the full/full
capacity-fill contradiction.  The no-group branch is ruled out by the fixed
pool merit comparison: if dropping the test does not expand either group's
pool, then `(P_full,P_full)` gives school `J2` strictly higher admitted
academic merit than `(P_full,P_sub)`, so `J2` has no incentive to drop.
