/--
Theorem 2, direct standard-Gaussian no-barrier bundle with the high-skill
delta comparison discharged from affine slope order.

This is the preferred static wrapper when the paper-parameter adapter has shown
that, at high skills, group A's full-policy standardized cutoff falls faster
than group B's while group B's test-free cutoff falls faster than group A's.
-/
theorem paper_theorem2_dropping_tests_without_barriers_standardGaussian_source_surface_of_slope_order
    {Group Policy : Type*} [DecidableEq Group] [DecidableEq Policy]
    (groupA groupB : Group) {Psub Pfull : Policy}
    {pi capacity quantile leftWeight priorPrecision subA subB testA testB : ℝ}
